oversample = RandomOverSampler()
x = x.values.reshape(x.shape[0], -1)
x, y = oversample.fit_resample(x, y)
x = np.array(x).reshape(-1, 28, 28, 3)



# Resize images to 32x32
x_resized = np.array([cv2.resize(img.astype(np.uint8), (32, 32)) for img in x])

print('Shape of X:', x_resized.shape)

In [5]:
"""Standardization and Splitting Data"""

x_resized = (x_resized - np.mean(x_resized)) / np.std(x_resized)
X_train, X_test, Y_train, Y_test = train_test_split(x_resized, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=1)

base_model = DenseNet121(input_shape=(32, 32, 3), include_top=False, weights='imagenet')
model = Sequential()
model.add(base_model)
model.add(Flatten())
model.add(Dense(256, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dropout(0.5))
model.add(Dense(128, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dropout(0.5))
model.add(Dense(7, activation='softmax'))

model.summary()

callback = tf.keras.callbacks.ModelCheckpoint(filepath='best_model.h5', monitor='val_accuracy', mode='max', verbose=1)
model.compile(loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
              optimizer='adam',
              metrics=['accuracy'])

history = model.fit(X_train,
                    Y_train,
                    validation_split=0.2,
                    batch_size=128,
                    epochs=20,
                    callbacks=[callback])

plt.plot(history.history['accuracy'])

from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, ConfusionMatrixDisplay

# Generate predictions
Y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
Y_pred = np.argmax(Y_pred, axis=1)

# Create confusion matrix
cm = confusion_matrix(Y_test, Y_pred)

# Define class names and corresponding labels
class_names = ['akiec', 'bcc', 'bkl', 'df', 'mel', 'nv', 'vasc']
class_names_labels = ['Actinic keratoses and intraepithelial carcinoma', 
                      'Basal cell carcinoma', 
                      'Benign keratosis-like lesions', 
                      'Dermatofibroma', 
                      'Melanoma', 
                      'Melanocytic nevi', 
                      'Vascular lesions']

# Plot confusion matrix
cm_display = ConfusionMatrixDisplay(confusion_matrix=cm, display_labels=class_names_labels)

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 8))
cm_display.plot(ax=ax, cmap=plt.cm.Blues)
plt.title('Confusion Matrix')
plt.xlabel('Predicted Label')
plt.ylabel('True Label')
plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
